Who wants to work on the weekends? Relax and enjoy your time off with friends and family, knowing that your light bill is taking a break, too. During the week, we deduct the electricity you use from your balance as you use it, but on Saturdays and Sundays we won’t charge you a thing. Zip. Zero. Nada. That’s 48 hours of free electricity between midnight on Friday to midnight on Sunday.

¿Quién quiere trabajar los fines de semana? Relajarse y disfrutar de su tiempo libre con amigos y familiares, sabiendo que su factura de la luz está tomando un descanso, también. Durante la semana, deducimos la electricidad que usa de su saldo medida que lo use, pero los sábados y domingos no se le cobrará nada. Cremallera. Cero. Nada. En total 48 horas de electricidad libre entre la media noche del viernes a la medianoche del domingo.

Take a load off at the end of the day. Rest easy, knowing that your light bill is sleeping while you do. During the day, we deduct the electricity you use from your balance as you use it, but overnight we won’t charge you a thing. Do the dishes, take a shower, run the laundry and crank up the AC between 8pm and 6am.

Tomar una carga al final del día. Descansa tranquilo sabiendo que su factura de la luz está durmiendo mientras lo hace. Average price calculation is based on 2,000 kWh and a standard usage profile over 12 months including 32% of total consumption on weekends, and includes the free weekend energy charge. Your average price for electricity will vary based on your usage times and days used. Only changes in law or regulatory charges allowed by the Public Utility Commission can change your price. Savings will vary according to time of usage. TDSP Monthly Charges are the fixed charges from the transmission and distribution service provider and are passed through without mark-up. TDSP Weekday Charges include all recurring consumption charges from TDSP and are passed through without mark-up. The free energy charge will be reflected on your monthly bill and is included in the average price calculation. Reliant reserves the right to discontinue this plan without notice.

[SpecialTerms]: Tomar una carga al final del día. Descansa tranquilo sabiendo que su factura de la luz está durmiendo mientras lo hace. Durante el día, deducimos la electricidad que usa de su saldo medida que lo use, pero durante la noche no se le cobrará nada. Lavar los platos, tomar una ducha, ejecute el servicio de lavandería y suba el aire acondicionado 8 p.m.-6 a.m.

Take a load off at the end of the day. Rest easy, knowing that your light bill is sleeping while you do. During the day, we deduct the electricity you use from your balance as you use it, but overnight we won’t charge you a thing. Do the dishes, take a shower, run the laundry and crank up the AC between 8pm and 6am.

¿Quién quiere trabajar los fines de semana? Relajarse y disfrutar de su tiempo libre con amigos y familiares, sabiendo que su factura de la luz está tomando un descanso, también. Durante la semana, deducimos la electricidad que usa de su saldo medida que lo use, pero los sábados y domingos no se le cobrará nada. Cremallera. Cero. Nada. En total 48 horas de electricidad libre entre la media noche del viernes a la medianoche del domingo.

Who wants to work on the weekends? Relax and enjoy your time off with friends and family, knowing that your light bill is taking a break, too. During the week, we deduct the electricity you use from your balance as you use it, but on Saturdays and Sundays we won’t charge you a thing. Zip. Zero. Nada. That’s 48 hours of free electricity between midnight on Friday to midnight on Sunday.

The Reliant Solar Sell Back plan is for people with solar PV systems installed at their home. Sign up for the Reliant Solar Sell Back plan and complete your Grid Contribution Agreement to have sell-back savings automatically credited to your monthly Reliant bill for surplus electricity generated and returned to the grid. *Price changes on the 15th of every month. Price is determined on the monthly closing NYMEX natural gas prices and can vary greatly month to month.**A dual-register meter beyond the Smart Meter may be required to measure generation and consumption. The customer’s home generation system must be connected to the grid by their TDSP to receive monthly payments for their surplus generation as reported by their TDSP. The customer must be located in a competitive ERCOT market.

[SpecialTerms]: Who wants to work on the weekends? Relax and enjoy your time off with friends and family, knowing that your light bill is taking a break, too. During the week, we deduct the electricity you use from your balance as you use it, but on Saturdays and Sundays we won’t charge you a thing. Zip. Zero. Nada. That’s 48 hours of free electricity between midnight on Friday to midnight on Sunday.

¿Quién quiere trabajar los fines de semana? Relajarse y disfrutar de su tiempo libre con amigos y familiares, sabiendo que su factura de la luz está tomando un descanso, también. Durante la semana, deducimos la electricidad que usa de su saldo medida que lo use, pero los sábados y domingos no se le cobrará nada. Cremallera. Cero. Nada. En total 48 horas de electricidad libre entre la media noche del viernes a la medianoche del domingo.

Take a load off at the end of the day. Rest easy, knowing that your light bill is sleeping while you do.
